In large resealable plastic bag, combine Lawry's(R) Seasoned Salt and Lawry's(R) Seasoned Pepper; add chicken. Close bag and toss to coat. In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat Spread over medium heat and cook chicken, turning occasionally, 25 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. Remove chicken to platter and keep warm. Drain skillet, if desired. In same skillet, bring marmalade and hot pepper sauce to a boil over high heat, scraping up brown bits from bottom of pan. Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat to low and simmer, tossing to coat with glaze, 5 minutes or until heated through. Garnish, if desired, with orange slices.